@100  = ~Jarnip: New Bonus Merchant in the Adventurers Mart~
@101  = ~Must be installed on BG2, BGT, BG2EE or EET~
@102  = ~Jarnip~
@103  = ~Jarnip's Wares~
@104  = ~Heart of Fury +3~
@105  = ~This impressive two-handed sword originally belonged to the Tribe of the Great White Wyrm, a barbarian clan from Icewind Dale that worshipped the white dragon matriarch Icasaracht. After Icasaracht was slain by a group of adventurers, the clan scattered, and its heirloom fell into the hands of outsiders. Despite the passage of time, the sword has retained Icasaracht's enchantment, and you can feel it pulsing with cold, primal fury.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Physical Damage Resistance: +8% (15% for barbarians) 
– Maxmimum Hit Points: +10 (+20 for barbarians)

THAC0: +3
Damage: 1d10+3, +1 cold
Damage Type: Slashing
Speed Factor: 7
Proficiency Type: Two-Handed Sword
Type: Two-Handed
Requires:
15 Strength

Weight: 10~
@106  = ~Gilded Bulwark +2~
@107  = ~This may well be the most extravagant suit of armor ever forged in the Realms. It was commissioned at great expense by Sir Alrond, a wealthy nobleman from Athkatla who bribed his way into the ranks of the Order of the Radiant Heart. Eager to flaunt his newly acquired title, Alrond ordered an extraordinary suit of armor that no other knight could match. The result is indeed a masterpiece: ornate, intricate, and gleaming, this armor is virtually immune to enemy blows. Unfortunately, due to its complexity, it was also too heavy for Alrond to wear. Humiliated and financially ruined, he was forced to sell the plate and was shortly after slain by a gibberling. Though it reeks of vanity, this armor offers unmatched protection, provided its new owner has the strength to wear it.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Physical Damage Resistance: +5% (+12% for cavaliers)
– Charisma: +1 (+2 for cavaliers)
– Base AC: +1 (cavalier only)

Armor Class: -1 (-5 vs. slashing, -4 vs. piercing and missile)
Requires:
 18 Strength

Weight: 100~
@108  = ~Elaine +3~
@109  = ~This longbow is the pinnacle of Elven craftsmanship. It once belonged to a legendary Arcane Archer named Elaine, who fell defending the Elven city of Askavar over a thousand years ago. According to legend, Elaine's soul still resides within the bow, empowering its arrows with magical energy.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– +1 THAC0 and damage with missile weapons (elven races and fighter/mages)

Combat abilities:
– When no arrows are equipped, the bow fires missiles that are treated as +3 for the purposes of determining what enemies they can damage. The missiles receive +3, to hit including the bonus listed below, and deal a total of 1d6+3 piercing and 1d4 magic damage

THAC0: +3
Damage: 1d6+3 (piercing), +1d4 (magic)
Speed Factor: 4
Proficiency Type: Longbow
Type: Two-handed
Requires:
 10 Strength
 13 Intelligence

Weight: 3~
@110  = ~Moonshade +3~
@111  = ~Moonblades are magical longswords that were forged in ancient Myth Drannor. They are immensely valuable to the elves and are used in the long process of selecting a ruler for the isle of Evermeet. Normally, a moonblade chooses its owner, but this particular sword seems willing to be wielded by anyone of elven heritage. It retains a powerful enchantment that greatly improves its wielder's arcane and martial abilities.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Armor Class: +1
– Casting Speed: +1

THAC0: +3
Damage: 1d8+3 (slashing), +1 (magic)
Speed Factor: 2
Proficiency Type: Longsword
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 10 Strength
 13 Intelligence

Weight: 3~
@112  = ~Bloodstone Ranger's Hood~
@113  = ~This hood was crafted by the Wardens of the Bloodstone Gate, an elite circle of rangers who once patrolled the mountain passes of Damara. It is said that this hood sharpens the senses of its wearer, enabling them to detect danger from a safe distance and strike first.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Weapon Speed Factor: +1
– Visual Range: +1 (+2 for stalkers)
– Attacks per round: +1/2 (stalkers only)
– Protects against critical hits

Weight: 2~
@114  = ~Herbert's Rapier +2~
@115  = ~The rapier is a light, thrusting sword often associated with nobles, duelists, and swashbucklers. It is not a popular weapon in Baldur's Gate and Amn, where broader and heavier blades are preferred. This particular rapier once belonged to Herbert Schwarz, a renowned Waterdhavian duelist who famously won twenty-one duels against heavily armored knights without ever wearing armor himself.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Armor Class: +2
– Critical Hit Chance: +5% (double for swashbucklers and blades)
– Luck: +1 (swashbuckler only)

Combat abilities:
– Each hit improves the wielder's Armor Class by 1 for 3 rounds // ?? seems excesive

THAC0: +2
Damage: 1d6+2 (piercing)
Speed Factor: 2
Proficiency Type: Short Sword / Rapier
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 5 Strength
 14 Dexterity

Weight: 2~
@116  = ~Spell Bane +2~
@117  = ~This beautifully decorated shield is forged from blue steel and adorned with runes. According to legend, it was forged for a Rashemi warrior from Mulsantir who pledged to purge The Unapproachable East of the Red Wizards some hundred years ago. The shield is said to possess a blessing that thwarts attempts to dispel or remove magic, reflecting such spells back onto those who cast them. More than one arrogant Red Wizard has discovered too late that the safest target for a dispelling spell is not always the warrior carrying Spell Bane.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Armor Class: +3
– Magic Resistance: +7% (+12% for wizard slayers, 20% for inquisitors)
– Reflects all Dispel Magic effects back at their caster (wizard slayer and inquisitor only) // does this even work?

Requires:
 4 Strength

Weight: 3~
@118  = ~Eye of the Storm +3~
@119  = ~This obsidian spear is adorned with the symbol of Talos, the Storm Lord, etched just beneath its head. It likely belonged to a High Priest of Talos, as its single swing can summon terrifying thunder and rain. You can feel the air electrifying when you hold this fearsome weapon, but only Druids and Rangers will be able to control its wrath.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Electricity Damage: +20%

Combat abilities:
– 20% chance to cast Call Lightning on hit (4d8 damage, save vs. spell for half)
– Changes local weather to thunderstorm while in combat

THAC0: +3
Damage: 1d8+3 (piercing), +1 (electrical)
Speed Factor: 3
Proficiency Type: Spear
Type: Two-handed
Requires:
 12 Strength
 16 Wisdom

Weight: 5~
@120  = ~Circlet of the Drunken Master~
@121  = ~The Way of the Drunken Master is a monastic tradition that teaches its practitioners to relinquish control over their bodies and become one with alcoholic beverages. While their clumsy fighting style may appear unskilled, it actually conceals exceptionally precise movements that almost always catch opponents off guard. The followers of the Way of the Drunken Master spend most of their time in taverns, yet this magical circlet puts its wearer in a blissful state of alcoholic intoxication without any of the usual downsides.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Armor Class: +3
– THAC0 and Damage: +2 when attacking with fists
– Protects against critical hits
– The wearer is under a permanent state of alcohol intoxication. It has no negative impact on Luck or Saving Throws.

Weight: 3~
@122  = ~Judicator +3~
@123  = ~According to legends, Judicator was forged by archons of Mount Celestia and bestowed upon a mortal Justiciar of Tyr centuries ago. Since then, it has assisted innumerable battles against the forces of evil, even beyond Toril. Judicator shines with a divine light that blazes upon its foes, blinding the unworthy and smiting evil with holy radiance.

STATISTICS:

Combat abilities:
– On each hit, the target must Save vs. Spell or become blinded for 1 round
– 15% chance per hit of casting Holy Smite centered on the target (affects evil only, 6d4 damage, save vs. spell for half)

THAC0: +3
Damage: 2d4+4 (crushing), +3 vs. evil (magic)
Speed Factor: 1
Proficiency Type: War Hammer
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 9 Strength
 13 Wisdom

Weight: 6~
@124  = ~Kensai's Arm +2~
@125  = ~The blade of this katana is forged from a rippling, wave-patterned steel. It is so sharp that it can slice through a single strand of hair. Crafting a weapon of this quality clearly required meticulous effort and time, but its true power lies in the soul of the Kensai bound within. If the spirit senses that the wielder also follows the path of the Sword Saint, it awakens and helps to guide their arm.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Attacks per round: +1/2 (+1 for kensais)

Combat abilities:
– For 10 seconds after activating Kai, the chance to score a critical hit increases by 10% (kensai only)

THAC0: +2
Damage: 1d10+2 (slashing)
Speed Factor: 2
Proficiency Type: Katana
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 6 Strength

Weight: 5~
@126  = ~Obsidian Splint Mail +3~
@127  = ~This suit of splint mail is unlike any forged from ordinary iron or steel. Each interlocking plate has been painstakingly crafted from obsidian crystal, polished until it gleams in the dark. Though heavier than most armors of its kind, it offers formidable resistance to magic.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Magic Resistance: +8% (+15% for wizard slayers)
– Saving Throws: +1 (+2 for wizard slayers)

Armor Class: 1 (0 vs. piercing and missile, -1 vs. crushing)
Requires:
 15 Strength

Weight: 50~
@128  = ~Reghedmen Iron Circlet~
@129  = ~This bare iron band was the war-helm of one of the barbarian chieftains from the Reghed Glacier who led the failed assault on the Ten Towns centuries ago. Said to be quenched in the blood of fallen foes and blessed by Tempus, this circlet sharpens the senses in the heat of battle, allowing its wearer to strike with deadly rage.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– THAC0 and Damage: +1
– Slashing, Crushing, and Piercing Damage: +7%
– Each time the wearer is hit in combat, Slashing, Crushing, and Piercing Damage increases by further 7% for 1 round (Barbarians only) // stacks?
– Protects against critical hits

Weight: 1~
@130  = ~Iron Resolve +2~
@131  = ~The blade of this sword is plain and unremarkable, forged from dark, unpolished iron. Its worn grip and nicked blade suggest that it has seen countless battles. Though lacking ornament, the sword is exceptionally well balanced and is said to answer to the resolve of its wielder.

STATISTICS: 

Equipped abilities:
– When the wielder's Hit Points fall below 50%, <PRO_HESHE> gains +2 bonus to THAC0. When Hit Points fall below 25%, <PRO_HESHE> gains an additional +2 THAC0 bonus and a +5% bonus to Critical Hit chance. (Fighter only)

Combat abilities:
– 25% chance on hit to grant the wielder +1 bonus to damage for 1 turn

THAC0: +2
Damage: 2d4+2 (slashing)
Speed Factor: 5
Proficiency Type: Bastard Sword
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 11 Strength

Weight: 7~
@132  = ~Bloodlust +5~
@133  = ~Cursed Berserking Sword +5: Bloodlust

Waterdhavian parents often tell their children the tale of Bloodlust: a cursed berserking sword with an insatiable desire to murder that ultimately turns on its wielder to quench its thirst for blood. The moral of the story is to never accept unknown magical items from strangers, and the sword was thought to be nothing more than a legend. However, it now lays before you.

The crimson blade is covered in bloodmarks, suggesting it is hundreds of years old. If the legends are true, it has caused the death of thousands, and countless innocents have fallen victim to its malevolent influence. The origins of Bloodlust are unclear, but it is evident that it was created for one purpose: to kill without end and unleash carnage across the Realms. 

The curse of this sword permanently marks the wielder: their hair turns white and begins to fall out, while their skin becomes ghastly and riddled with blisters. Over time, they lose physical fortitude and wither from within. The only way to alleviate this affliction is through satiating the blade's desire for bloodshed, yet the curse itself may never be lifted.

Once equipped, this cursed sword cannot be removed or unequipped by any known spell or ritual. The wielder has no choice but to obey and continue the slaughter. Only death can grant freedom from its curse.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Permanently cursed without any possibility of removal beyond death
– Charisma: -5
– Constitution: -2
– Appearance changes: skin turns pale gray, hair becomes bone-white

Combat abilities:
– Murderous Wrath: On each hit, the wielder must Save vs. Death (-2 penalty) or go berserk for 2 rounds. When berserk, the movement rate is doubled and the base number of attacks per round is set to 5
– Dread Hunger: On each hit, the target must Save vs. Death or receive extra 2d4 magic damage. The stolen Hit Points are transferred to the wielder. This will not heal beyond the wielder's maximum
– Blood Lust: Killing an enemy restores 4d6 Hit Points and increases Strength, Dexterity, and Constitution by 1 for 1 turn

THAC0: +5
Damage: 2d4+5 (slashing)
Speed Factor: 3
Proficiency Type: Bastard Sword
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 10 Strength

Weight: 10~
@134  = ~Korgunth's Right Fist +2~
@135  = ~This heavy stone hammer once belonged to Korgunth Ironwarden, a dwarven defender from the Silver Marches. Unlike most dwarven defenders, Korgunth favored an aggressive two-handed fighting style, charging into enemy ranks with rage. Due to its sheer weight, his hammer, known as the "Right Fist," was capable of delivering devastating blows, especially against the traditional enemies of the dwarves: goblins, orcs, and giants.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– +5% Resistance to Slashing, Piercing, and Crushing Damage
– Strength: +1 (dwarves only)

THAC0: +2
Damage: 2d4+3 (crushing), extra +2d4 vs. goblins, orcs, and giants
Damage Type: crushing
Speed Factor: 2
Proficiency Type: War Hammer
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 16 Strength

Weight: 20~
@136  = ~Korgunth's Left Fist +2~
@137  = ~This heavy stone hammer once belonged to Korgunth Ironwarden, a dwarven defender from the Silver Marches. Unlike most dwarven defenders, Korgunth favored an aggressive two-handed fighting style, charging into enemy ranks with rage. The "Left Fist" was essential to Korgunth's martial techniques and allowed him to strike with deadly swiftness.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– +5% Resistance to Slashing, Piercing, and Crushing Damage
– Constitution: +1
– Attacks per round: +1/2 (dwarven defender only)

THAC0: +2
Damage: 2d4+3 (crushing)
Speed Factor: 2
Proficiency Type: War Hammer
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 16 Strength

Weight: 20~
@138  = ~Silver Watch +2~
@139  = ~The blade of this finely decorated halberd has gold-plated edges and is forged from shiny, polished steel. It was commissioned by the Grand Dukes of Baldur's Gate for the captain of the Flaming Fist's Honor Guard. Although forged for ceremonial purposes, the halberd is also lethal in combat. Its unusually long shaft and spike at the top allow the wielder to keep enemies at bay and stagger them with precise strikes. It is a beautiful weapon, equally suited for the battlefield and grand military parades.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Movement rate increased by a factor of 2

Combat abilities:
– Melee range increased by 50%
– On hit: 33% chance to stagger the target in place for 1 round and deal 1d10 piercing damage (no save)

THAC0: +2
Damage: 1d10+2 (slashing or piercing, whichever is better)
Speed Factor: 7
Proficiency Type: Halberd
Type: Two-handed
Requires:
 15 Strength
 12 Dexterity

Weight: 12~
@140  = ~Black Doom +2~
@141  = ~At first glance, this blackened iron shield seems old and unremarkable. However, upon closer inspection, you notice a faint symbol of Bane carved on its interior. It once belonged to a forsaken blackguard who ravaged the coast of Tethyr during one of its civil wars. Ultimately, the Banite was hunted down by the Loyal Order of Innocents, and his name was erased from recorded history.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Armor Class: +3 (+4 for Blackguards)
– Saving Throws: +1 (+2 for Blackguards)
– Fire and Cold Resistance: +20%

Combat abilities:
– Casts Doom on whoever hits the wielder: -2 penalty to THAC0 and Saving Throws for 1 turn

Requires:
 9 Strength~
@142  = ~Herbert's Black Mantle~
@143  = ~Herbert Schwarz was a famous Waterdhavian duelist whose adventures along the Sword Coast left behind as many tavern brawls as humiliated opponents. It is said that nearly every inn between Waterdeep and Baldur's Gate eventually displayed a notice declaring that the adventurer was no longer a welcome guest. Whether he departed on his own or was driven by a coalition of organized innkeepers, the tales claim Herbert eventually wandered south in search of new adventures.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Armor Class: +1
– Melee THAC0 and damage: +1
– Melee Critical Hit chance: +5% (swashbuckler and blade only)

Weight: 2~
@144  = ~Helm of the Faithful~
@145  = ~A relic of the Lathanderite church, Helm of the Faithful is said to be imbued with the divine essence of the "Armor of Faith" spell. While the protection it provides may appear modest, any experienced knight will immediately recognize its value, especially on the most perilous journeys.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Damage Resistance: +5%
– Armor Class: +1
– Saving Throws: +1
– Protects against critical hits

Weight: 2~
@146  = ~Wayfarer +4~
@147  = ~This leather armor was crafted for the leader of the Wardens of the Bloodstone Gate, an elite circle of rangers who once patrolled the mountain passes of Damara. The group was known for their ambush tactics, and its equipment was specifically crafted to support long mountaineous journeys. This armor is decorated with fox fur and surprisingly lightweight, enabling its wearer to attack swiftly and disappear immediately afterwards.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Move Silently and Hide In Shadows: +10
– Movement rate increased by 2
– Immunity to fatigue
– Backstab multiplier: +1 (stalkers only)

Armor Class: 3 (1 vs. slashing, 2 vs. piercing and missile)
Requires:
 3 Strength

Weight: 3~
@148  = ~Slayer of Men +2~
@149  = ~When the first settlements of the Ten Towns were established some three hundred years ago, the barbarian clans vowed to drive the so-called "civilized" men from their ancestral lands. They soon launched a brutal campaign, conducting devastating raids on neighboring towns. It is said that one of the barbarian chieftains was capable of cleaving through multiple foes with a single swing of his two-handed axe, which soon became known as the "Slayer of Men." The bloodstains on its blade serve as a vivid reminder of this violent period in Icewind Dale's history.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Armor Class: -2
– Attacks per round: +1/2 (berserkers and barbarians only)

Combat abilities:
– Each successful hit deals extra 1d10 slashing damage to all enemies within 3 ft. in front of the wielder. Affected targets must save vs. Death or fall on the ground for 1 round.

THAC0: +2
Damage: 1d12+2 (slashing)
Speed Factor: 7
Proficiency Type: Axe
Type: Two-handed
Requires:
 16 Strength

Weight: 15~
@150  = ~Torm's Gauntlets~
@151  = ~These gauntlets are said to have been worn by Torm himself during the Time of Troubles. Whether the legend is true or not, they grant the wearer a powerful blessing, strengthening their resolve and improving their divine spellcasting skills.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Armor Class: +1
– Saving Throws: +1
– Casting speed: +1 (clerics and paladins only)
– Divine Casting Level: +1 (clerics and paladins only)

Weight: 1~
